goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is any correlation between distance and delay, and if longer flights tend to have more delays.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flights over time?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the trend of flights over time and identify any seasonality or patterns in flight schedules.

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].mean(), color='red', label='Mean delay = {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].median(), color='green', label='Median delay = {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data['distance'], vert=False, showmeans=True, meanline=True, 
               labels=['Distance'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    ax.set_title('What is the average distance of flights?')
    ax.axvline(x=data['distance'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', 
               label='Mean Distance: {:.2f}'.format(data['distance'].mean()))
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data = data.groupby('origin').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    data = data.sort_values('counts', ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data['origin'], data['counts'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Origin Airport')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    ax.set_title('What is the most common origin airport?')
    ax.axhline(y=data['counts'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Most common origin airport: {data.iloc[0]["origin"]} ({data.iloc[0]["counts"]})')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['delay', 'distance']]
    plt.scatter(data['distance'], data['delay'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median Delay')
    plt.xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    plt.ylabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between distance and delay?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data.index, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of flights over time?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
